### Real-Time Trading API Tests
### Make sure the application is running before executing these requests

@host = http://localhost:5000
@host_https = https://localhost:5001

### Quick Start - Monitor BTCUSDT with default settings (15m, Combined strategy)
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/quick-start/BTCUSDT?autoTrade=false

### Quick Start - Monitor ETHUSDT 
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/quick-start/ETHUSDT?autoTrade=false

### Start Custom Monitoring - BTC with 1h interval
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symbol": "BTCUSDT",
  "interval": "1h",
  "strategy": "combined",
  "autoTrade": false
}

### Start Monitoring - ETH with RSI strategy on 15m
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symbol": "ETHUSDT",
  "interval": "15m",
  "strategy": "rsi",
  "autoTrade": false
}

### Start Monitoring - BNB with MACD strategy on 4h
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symbol": "BNBUSDT",
  "interval": "4h",
  "strategy": "macd",
  "autoTrade": false
}

### Start Monitoring with AUTO-TRADING (Use with caution!)
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symbol": "BTCUSDT",
  "interval": "15m",
  "strategy": "combined",
  "autoTrade": true
}

### Get All Active Monitoring Sessions
GET {{host}}/realtime/monitor/active

### Get Latest Signals for All Monitored Symbols
GET {{host}}/realtime/signals

### Stop Monitoring - BTCUSDT
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/BTCUSDT

### Stop Monitoring - ETHUSDT
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/ETHUSDT

### Stop Monitoring - BNBUSDT
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/BNBUSDT

###
### Example Workflow: Monitor multiple pairs and check signals
###

### Step 1: Start monitoring BTC, ETH, and BNB
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/quick-start/BTCUSDT?autoTrade=false

###
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/quick-start/ETHUSDT?autoTrade=false

###
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/quick-start/BNBUSDT?autoTrade=false

### Step 2: Check active sessions
GET {{host}}/realtime/monitor/active

### Step 3: Wait for signals (15 minutes for 15m interval)
### Then check latest signals
GET {{host}}/realtime/signals

### Step 4: If you see a good signal, you can manually place an order
### (See TradingBot.ApiService.http for order placement examples)

### Step 5: Stop monitoring when done
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/BTCUSDT

###
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/ETHUSDT

###
POST {{host}}/realtime/monitor/stop/BNBUSDT

